ts=2026-06-12T11:27:15.392Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="Footer format for summarized lectures: `_X min read (source: Y min)_` where X is summary read time and Y is original source read time." tags=footer,format,summarize
ts=2026-06-12T11:27:16.607Z type=preference scope=opencode content="When user says \"remember\", use memory tools (memory_[remember|update]) to store the information rather than just acknowledging it." tags=workflow,memory
ts=2026-06-12T12:19:43.961Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="It's okay to have summary equal in readtime to the source. Only trim if it's greater than it." tags=readtime,trimming,summarize
ts=2026-06-12T12:57:10.211Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="Don't remove the `# Course Name - [Lecture|Section|Task|Assignment] N` header from the summary." tags=header,format,summarize
ts=2026-06-12T13:18:15.317Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="When explaining concepts, use Mermaid flowcharts (Mermaid code blocks do not count toward read time). Only include a flowchart if it adds value; otherwise, skip it." tags=mermaid,flowcharts,format
ts=2026-06-12T16:27:17.564Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="When the user provides code snippets to include in summaries, do NOT copy them verbatim (unless told). Always refactor to match established conventions."
ts=2026-06-12T17:52:31.383Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="Always re-run `readtime` after adding code blocks to a summary file — formatting markdown may increase read time. Don't trust the previous readtime value once content changes."
